<subSubSection pageId="392" pageNumber="393" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="392" pageNumber="393">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="392" pageNumber="393">
This species is found along the Atlantic and Gulf of Mexico coasts from the Maritime Provinces (Lindroth 1963b: 373; Bousquet 1987a: 121) to southern Florida including the Keys (Leng 1915: 572), west to southeastern Texas (Wickham 1897: 104; Casey 1918: 124, as 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="392" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="constrictum" subSpecies="civile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="392" pageNumber="393">Bembidion constrictum civile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The records from Ohio (Everly 1938: 141), Indiana (Wolcott and Montgomery 1933: 125), South Dakota (Kirk and Balsbaugh 1975: 19), 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Nebraska”">&quot;Nebraska&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Hayward 1897: 108), Kansas (Knaus 1887: 87; Snow 1903: 193), and &quot;New Mexico&quot; (Hayward 1897: 108) probably refer to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="LaFerte-Senectere" baseAuthorityYear="1841" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="392" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridicolle">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="392" pageNumber="393">Bembidion viridicolle</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="LaFerté-Sénectère">LaFerte-Senectere</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
